Cut pound cake evenly into six slices and place on dessert plates. Place pears in microwave-safe bowl, sprinkle with sugar, and cover; microwave on HIGH 4 minutes or until tender. Let stand 5 minutes. Place white chocolate, pudding, and cream in second microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on HIGH 2 minutes or until hot. Let stand 3 minutes; then stir until smooth. Drain pears, just before serving, and spoon over cake slices. Pour sauce over pears; top with raspberries and serve.